# SEO & Discoverability (mandatory release gate)

SEO is **not** a separate feature. It is a **release requirement** for every route, page, template, and API-backed surface in this repo.

Do **not** mark a feature COMPLETE until functional tests, typecheck, build, responsive checks, a11y, **and** SEO validation pass.

## Before finishing any new page / route / template

Review and satisfy where appropriate:

- Technical SEO, on-page SEO, semantic/entity SEO
- Internal linking & discoverability (no orphans)
- Indexing (robots, canonical, sitemap `lastmod`)
- Structured data (JSON-LD) where it fits the page type
- Core Web Vitals targets: **LCP &lt; 2.5s**, **INP &lt; 200ms**, **CLS &lt; 0.1**
- Accessibility + mobile-first
- Multilingual SEO: **Hindi-first**; English where appropriate; correct hreflang; **no mixed-language metadata**

## Page must include (when appropriate)

- Unique **title** + unique **meta description** (never duplicates)
- Canonical URL, Open Graph, Twitter Card, robots directives
- Breadcrumbs, proper heading hierarchy, semantic HTML
- Descriptive image alt, sized images, lazy-load (preload only when justified)
- JSON-LD where appropriate (Article, BreadcrumbList, FAQPage, WebSite, Organization, etc.)
- Internal links + related content; FAQ only when it genuinely helps
- Human-readable URLs; sitemap inclusion with accurate lastmod
- hreflang when multiple languages exist

Use existing helpers: `src/lib/seo/metadata.ts` (`buildPageMetadata`, `buildUtilityPageMetadata`), `src/lib/seo/json-ld.ts`, sitemap builders under `src/lib/seo/`.

## Content

Write for users first. One primary intent per page. Avoid keyword stuffing, hidden keywords, doorway pages, thin auto-pages, filler, or duplicated paragraphs. Every page needs useful unique information.

## Programmatic SEO

Only generate district/city/category/rates pages when **meaningful content exists**. Each generated page needs unique title, description, intro, FAQ (if useful), related links, structured data, breadcrumbs. Never mass-generate empty pages.

## Internal linking

Connect Story → Category → District → Topic → Related → Market/Weather/Live/Author/Tags where relevant. Important pages must be reachable via contextual links.

## Backlink readiness

Prefer pages worth citing: original datasets, local stats, explainers, timelines, archives, calculators, dashboards (mandi, weather, elections), verified rates, district profiles. Do **not** artificially manufacture backlinks.

## Performance / rendering

Prefer Server Components; SSR/ISR when appropriate; avoid unnecessary client JS.

## Indexing exceptions

Utility/account/offline-device pages may be `noindex` when they are personal or non-public — still give unique titles/descriptions and correct robots. Public editorial hubs must be indexable.

**Do not** force `/admin`, `/api`, `/dashboard`, `/debug`, or other non-public surfaces into the public sitemap. Keep them disallowed / noindex per existing `robots.ts` and layout metadata. Sitemap entries are only for intentionally indexable URLs.

This gate improves discoverability hygiene. It does **not** guarantee backlinks, rankings, or Search Console outcomes.

## Quality gate checklist (all required for COMPLETE)

- [ ] Functional tests pass
- [ ] Typecheck passes
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] Responsive checks pass
- [ ] Accessibility checks pass
- [ ] SEO audit passes (metadata, headings, links, CWV posture)
- [ ] Structured data validates (when present)
- [ ] Sitemap updated / included when indexable
- [ ] Internal links verified
- [ ] Metadata verified (unique title + description + canonical)

Full policy: `docs/jandarpan-seo-quality-gate.md`
